condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :Section 1 A. (a) | Description :Maintain the Sindh Skills Development Leadership Team, for the strategic policyguidance and oversight of the implementation of the three components of the Project | Frequency :Quarterly

Finance Agreement :Section 1 A. (b) | Description :Cause BBSYDP to maintain a provincial steering committee in order to providestrategic leadership, policy guidance and general oversight to BBSYDP in the carrying out of Com. 1 of the Project | Frequency:Quarterly
Finance Agreement :Section 1 A. (c) | Description :BBSYDP to maintain a provincial coordination unit (the PCU) headed by anexperienced Project Coordinator | Frequency :Yearly
Finance Agreement :Section 1 A. (d) | Description :Maintain a project team (STEVTA PT) headed by an experienced Project Coordinator| Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Section 1 A. (e) | Description :Maintain an independent evaluation committee to carry out the evaluation ofprograms to be established or upgraded under Component 2 | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Section 1. C. 3 (a)- (c) | Description :BBSYDP shall enter into contracts or agreements with Training Providerswhich shall include performance-based system, automatic disqualification and obligation to report regularly. | Frequency :Quarterly

Finance Agreement :Section 1. C. 5 | Description :BBSYDP pay the Stipends/Relocation Allowances to the Trainees in a timelyfashion, subject to the Trainees' on-going compliance with/maintenance of the eligibility criteria | Frequency :Monthly
Finance Agreement :Section 1. C. 6 | Description :BBSYDP to adopt an easily accessible grievance redressal mechanism | Due Date:31-Jul-2012
Finance Agreement :Section 1. C. 7 | Description :BBSYDP to implement a comprehensive documentation and record keeping database |Frequency :Quarterly

Finance Agreement :Section 1. D. 3 | Description :STEVTA to ensure that the selection of programs to be established, or upgraded iscarried out in an open, transparent and competitive manner | Due Date :31-Dec-2011
Finance Agreement :Section 1. D. 4 | Description :STEVTA shall enter into a memorandum of understanding with each selectedvocational/technical training institution, | Due Date :31-Dec-2011
Finance Agreement :Section 1. F. (a) | Description :All 6 types of documents related to Component 1, are made available andpublicly accessible at the website of BBSYDP | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Section 1. F. (b) | Description :All 6 types of documents related to Components 2 and 3 of the Project are madeavailable and publicly accessible at the website of STEVTA | Frequency :Yearly
Finance Agreement :Section II B. 4. (a) and (b) | Description :Departmental Accounts Committee meetings held to discuss auditreports for STEVTA and BBSYDP for FY09 and FY10. | Due Date :30-Jun-2011

Finance Agreement :Section II B. 4. (a) | Description :STEVTA to appoint and thereafter maintain throughout the period ofimplementation of the Project, an internal audit director. | Due Date :30-Jun-2011
Finance Agreement :Section II B. 4. (a) | Description :STEVTA will appoint a chartered accounting firm to audit financialstatements for FY09 and FY10. | Due Date :30-Jun-2011

Finance Agreement :Section II B. 4. (b) | Description :BBSYDP to engage the services of a chartered firm of accountants or aqualified accountant for carrying out Project's internal audits | Due Date :31-Dec-2011
